# PWA manifest sync (mandatory procedure)

When the user asks to change app name, favicon, PWA icons, `theme_color`,
`background_color`, or install shortcuts:

1. Read **`agent-os/skills/pwa-manifest/SKILL.md`** first.
2. Read **`docs/reference/pwa-manifest-and-app-icon.md`** (rules + checklist).
3. Edit **`src/core/config/app-manifest.ts`** before `public/manifest.webmanifest`.
4. Sync **`index.html`**, **`page-head.ts`** (`APP_DESCRIPTION`), and PNGs (if SVG changed).
5. Run **`pnpm test:unit src/core/config/app-manifest.test.ts`** and **`pnpm validate:public`**.

**Do not** hand-edit manifest JSON without updating `buildWebManifest()` — the drift test will fail CI.

**Colors** must stay aligned with the default preset (`#ffffff` background, `#0a0a0a` theme/shell).

**Icons:** Lucide Boxes on `#0a0a0a` tile; regenerate PNGs with `rsvg-convert`, not `sips`.
